=== Why Action is Urgent for Non-Severe Cases

#include "../../key-points/key-the-lesson-from-pediatric-recovery.typ"

    - *Prevention of progression*: Approximately 25% of ME/CFS patients are severe/very severe @Rowe2017pediatric. Many started as mild-moderate and progressed due to continued overexertion @Lacourt2022prognosis.
    - *Window of opportunity*: Earlier intervention may prevent immune exhaustion phase (Achievement @ach:cytokine-duration).
    - *Quality of life*: Even mild ME/CFS significantly impairs function and well-being; deserves treatment.
    - *Biomarker evidence*: Cytokine dysregulation and immune cell abnormalities are detectable even in mild ME/CFS @Hornig2015 @Giloteaux2023.

